&lt;p&gt;The Customer Service Representative serves an important role for TravelInsurance.com. They are usually the first point of contact for people seeking new travel insurance policies or seeking assistance with existing travel insurance policies.&amp;nbsp;They are responsible for answering the phone and assisting qualified leads from our website, as well as assisting existing customers with policy assistance via our live chat platform and phone system.&amp;nbsp;Our primary goal is to provide an A+ customer experience to our customers while being friendly, knowledgeable and professional.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideal candidates will be located in CST or EST. Hours of operation are 8am-6pm EST.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a first point of contact for prospective and existing customers by answering inbound phone calls and responding through live chat in a professional, friendly, and timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver an A+ customer experience by actively listening, identifying customer needs, and providing accurate guidance on new and existing travel insurance policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use a consultative sales approach to qualify leads, ask thoughtful questions, recommend appropriate coverage options, and help customers select the best solution for their travel plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist existing policyholders with service-related questions, policy support, and general troubleshooting while ensuring clear communication and follow-through.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a strong working knowledge of TravelInsurance.com products, carrier offerings, policy details, and key coverage differences in order to communicate information clearly and confidently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately document customer interactions and manage multiple conversations or tasks at once while maintaining attention to detail and service quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a positive, proactive, and customer-focused mindset while contributing to team goals and supporting a high-quality customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 1 year of sales experience required; customer service experience in the travel insurance industry strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current travel and/or property &amp;amp; casualty insurance license required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be authorized to work in the United States.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to explain coverage options and policy details clearly to customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inbound call center experience preferred, along with the ability to multitask effectively in a fast-paced, customer-facing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

