&lt;p&gt;Integrated Specialty Coverages, LLC (ISC) is a growth stage technology and data-driven commercial MGA and insurance wholesaler leading innovation in the market.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Backed by one of the leading private equity firms, Onex Partners, and led by a forward-thinking management team, ISC is combining the worlds of insurance and technology to create an Insurtech powerhouse. As a leading online distributor of insurance products for a range of industries and “Main Street USA”, we are looking for the right people to help us in our mission of achieving exponential growth. We strive to be the number one place to go for brokers and agents to source insurance. To accomplish this, we’re building a digitally focused team that deeply understands the intersection between user experience, data, and AI/ML to optimize the way we engage with our customers and partners.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Channel Specialist, Paid Search &amp;amp; Affiliate Marketing is an execution-focused role on ISC&#39;s Retail Marketing Team (RMT), sitting within the Channel Acquisition Team reporting to the Channel Manager. This person is the operational engine behind ISC&#39;s two highest-priority performance acquisition channels-&amp;nbsp; paid search and affiliate/aggregator partnerships. The Senior Channel Specialist owns the hands-on, daily execution of building and managing campaigns, trafficking creative assets, monitoring partner placements, reconciling billing, and maintaining the data hygiene that keeps both channels performing accurately. This role is ideal for a detail-oriented performance marketer who thrives in a high-volume, multi-business unit environment with direct revenue impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute day-to-day paid search campaign management across Google Ads and Microsoft Ads for all active ISC retail brands, including campaign builds, ad copy trafficking, bid adjustments, keyword list maintenance, negative keyword management, and quality score monitoring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support affiliate and aggregator channel operations across the ISC portfolio: manage creative asset trafficking and partner onboarding logistics, maintain active placements for partners including LendingTree, NerdWallet, Red Ventures, Forbes, Money Group, The Knot, Cvent, and others, and action performance-based optimizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor paid search and affiliate campaign performance daily; flag anomalies in conversion rates, impression share, CPL, and partner attribution to the Channel Manager and escalate data integrity issues to the Snr. Manager Marketing Analytics / Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate creative production and asset management across both channels: brief and traffic paid search ad copy updates, maintain the affiliate creative asset library (IAB banner sets, co-branded landing pages, text links, partner email templates), and manage seasonal or campaign-based refresh cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own monthly affiliate vendor billing reconciliation across all active partners; maintain accurate budget tracking records and surface material pacing variances to the Channel Manager and Finance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure UTM parameter governance, pixel tagging accuracy, and affiliate tracking integrity across all active placements in coordination with the Snr. Manager Marketing Analytics / Operations; actively flag and help resolve attribution discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Channel Manager in preparing weekly performance summaries, monthly channel reports, and competitive intelligence research across paid search and affiliate for the ISC retail brand portfolio.&lt;/li&gt;
